data.chText: 胚；胚胎；（尤指受孕后八周内的）人类胚胎
data.enText: a young animal or plant in the very early stages of development before birth, or before coming out of its egg or seed, especially a human egg in the first eight weeks after fertilization
an embryo politician (= one who is not yet very experienced)

data.chText: 在胚胎阶段；在萌芽时期；尚未成熟
data.enText: existing but not yet fully developed

data.chText: 这个想法在他早期的小说中已初见端倪。
data.enText: The idea already existed in embryo in his earlier novels.

simple_means.memory_skill: em 使… + bry 发芽 + o 抽象名词 → 胚胎，萌芽

means: (尤指受孕后八周内的)人类胚胎

data.chText: 在胚胎阶段；在萌芽时期；尚未成熟
data.enText: existing but not yet fully developed

data.chText: 这个想法在他早期的小说中已初见端倪。
data.enText: The idea already existed in embryo in his earlier novels.

tr: an animal organism in the early stages of growth and differentiation that in higher forms merge into fetal stages but in lower forms terminate in commencement of larval life
(botany) a minute rudimentary plant contained within a seed or an archegonium

value.def: An embryo is an unborn animal or human being in the very early stages of development.

example.ex: The embryo lives in the amniotic cavity.
...the remarkable resilience of very young embryos.
example.tran: 早期胚胎非凡的适应力

value.def: An embryo idea, system, or organization is in the very early stages of development, but is expected to grow stronger.

example.ex: They are an embryo party of government...
example.tran: 他们这个政党有望组建政府，但目前还不成熟。

example.ex: It was an embryo idea rather than a fully worked proposal.
example.tran: 这只是初步的想法，并非成形的提议。

value.tran: (想法、体系或机构)萌芽阶段的，初期的

value.def: Something that is in embryo is at a very early stage of its development.

example.ex: These developments were foreseen in embryo more than a decade ago.
example.tran: 这些发展早在十多年前的萌芽阶段就已预见到。
